cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MA, cs.CYBER, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the study of viral campaigns on the Internet, which involves social interactions and the use of mathematical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions the use of mathematical models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MA (Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the time-generations relationship, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of individuals in the campaign, which could place it in cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
